The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for classifying molecules with respect to protein binding, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of attribution methods to interpret the learned mechanisms of the neural network, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of dataset bias and the need for regularization, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
